      "raw_text": "Saturday, and speak.\n\n\nElizabeth Gurley Flynn, woman\nagitator of the |. w. W., will speak\nthis evening in the Turner hall, on\nThird avenue, between Browne and\nDivision streets.\n\n\n!. w. w. Committee Statement.\n\n\nSpokane, Wash, Dec. 20. 1909.\nTo Whom 1t May Concern:\n\n\nThe article appearing in the\nSpokesmanReview of Sunday\nmorning, December 10th, stating\nthat the |. w. w. had surrendered\nin the fight for free speech is\nwithout foundation.\n\n\nNo member of the executive\ncommittee has been to see Burns\nDREAMY other detective or official\nof the Spokane police force.\n\n\nNo member of the committee or\nthe |. w. w. told Burns or any one\nelse that the |. w. w. had called\nthe fight off.\n\n\nFor the information of all who\nare interested we will state that so\n\n\nCont;pnad IN D,ne Tuo"
